 Os-harm: A bench-\n1449\tmark for measuring safety of computer use agents.arXiv\n1450\tpreprint arXiv:2506.14866, 2025.\n1451\tLandis, J. R. and Koch, G. G. The measurement of observer\n1452\tagreement for categorical data.biometrics, pp. 159–174,\n1453\t1977.\n1454\tLiao, Z., Jones, J., Jiang, L., Ning, Y ., Fosler-Lussier, E.,\n1455\tSu, Y ., Lin, Z., and Sun, H. Redteamcua: Realistic\n1456\tadversarial testing of computer-use agents in hybrid web-\n1457\tos environments.arXiv preprint arXiv:2505.21936, 2025.\n1458\tLiu, Y ., Xu, R., Wang, X., Jia, Y ., and Gong, N. Z. Wain-\n1459\tjectbench: Benchmarking prompt injection detections for\n1460\tweb agents.arXiv preprint arXiv:2510.01354, 2025.\n1461\tLuo, H., Dai, S., Ni, C., Li, X., Zhang, G., Wang, K., Liu,\n1462\tT., and Salam, H. Agentauditor: Human-level safety\n1463\tand security evaluation for llm agents.arXiv preprint\n1464\tarXiv:2506.00641, 2025a.\n1465\tLuo, W., Dai, S., Liu, X., Banerjee, S., Sun, H., Chen, M.,\n1466\tand Xiao, C. Agrail: A lifelong agent guardrail with\n1467\teffective and adaptive safety detection.arXiv preprint\n1468\tarXiv:2502.11448, 2025b.\n1469\tLynch, A., Wright, B., Larson, C., Ritchie, S. J., Minder-\n1470\tmann, S., Hubinger, E., Perez, E., and Troy, K. Agentic\n1471\tmisalignment: how llms could be insider threats.arXiv\n1472\tpreprint arXiv:2510.05179, 2025.\n1473\tMeng, K., Huang, V ., Steinhardt, J., and Schwettmann,\n1474\tS. Introducing docent. https://transluce.org/\n1475\tintroducing-docent, March 2025.\n1476\tNaik, A., Quinn, P., Bosch, G., Goun´e, E., Zabala, F. J. C.,\n1477\tBrown, J. R., and Young, E. J. Agentmisalignment: Mea-\n1478\tsuring the propensity for misaligned behaviour in llm-\n1479\tbased agents.arXiv preprint arXiv:2506.04018, 2025.\n1480\tOpenAI. Gpt-5.1: A smarter, more conversational chat-\n1481\tgpt, 2025a. URL https://openai.com/index/\n1482\tgpt-5-1/.\n1483\tOpenAI. Operator system card., 2025b. URL\n1484\thttps://cdn.openai.com/operator_\n148